## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| **Critical** | 6 |
| **Medium** | 2 |

This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test class. Every public method on `ProductCatalog` is called (achieving high line coverage), but almost nothing is actually verified. These tests will pass even if the production code is completely broken — a bug could ship in any method and none of these tests would catch it.

---

### Critical Findings

#### 1. Coverage Touching (Systemic)

The entire class follows a pattern of calling each method with no assertion or only `Assert.IsNotNull`. This inflates coverage to ~95% while verifying almost nothing.

**Tests with zero assertions (always pass):**

| Test Method | Line |
|---|---|
| `AddProduct_Works` | 17–21 |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` | 33–36 |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` | 39–43 |
| `GetProductCount_Works` | 64–66 |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` | 69–74 |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` | 85–88 |

These tests can **never fail** unless the production code throws an unhandled exception.

**Concrete fixes:**

```csharp
// BEFORE – AddProduct_Works (line 17)
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_Works()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);
}

// AFTER
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_StoresProduct_RetrievableBySku()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);

    var retrieved = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual("Widget", retrieved?.Name);
    Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, retrieved?.Price);
}
```

```csharp
// BEFORE – UpdatePrice_Works (line 33)
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);

// AFTER
[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_ChangesStoredPrice()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);

    Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")?.Price);
}
```

```csharp
// BEFORE – ApplyBulkDiscount_Works (line 69)
_catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);

// AFTER
[TestMethod]
public void ApplyBulkDiscount_ReducesPricesByFraction()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 10.00m));
    _catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);

    Assert.AreEqual(9.00m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")?.Price);
}
